{
  "texts": [
    "These basic templates only provide basic functionalities to maintain the fundamental operation of the library.",
    "With this templatized design, we can easily extend a new template within any module, enabling reusability when implementing new models.In addition to the aforementioned four modules, there are two additional modules (i.e., configuration reading and log storage) that are shared by all models.",
    "For configuration reading, we prioritize and categorize the configurations from four flexible configuration portals.",
    "This allows us to identify five categories of configurations, where four categories correspond to the four templatized modules, and the last category involves framework-specific configurations.",
    "For Log Storage, we store logs from failed or ongoing runs in temporary storage, while successful run logs are stored archivally."
  ]
}